# Greg CRM — MVP Walkthrough

**Your contacts are markdown files. Your agent does the work.**

Built as a Vite + React web app at `/Users/canerden/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/gregg-crm/`.

## What We Built

A local-first CRM with a clean, dark Linear/Notion-inspired aesthetic — designed for founders and startup operators, not just engineers.

### Homepage & Sidebar
![Homepage with sidebar navigation, contact list, and welcome state](homepage_1772724679047.png)

- **Sidebar** with search, status filters (Hot/Warm/Cold), Needs Follow-up view, and tag navigation
- **Contact list** with avatars, company names, and color-coded status dots
- **Welcome state** with ⌘K hint and "Create Your First Contact" CTA

### Contact Detail View
![Sarah Chen contact detail with metadata, tags, quick actions, and activity timeline](contact_detail_sarah_1772724706421.png)

- Name, role, company with gradient avatar
- **Status badge** + **tag pills** (investor, series-a, etc.)
- **Quick actions**: Email, Call, LinkedIn, Log Activity
- **Metadata grid**: email, phone, last contacted, created date
- **Markdown-rendered** notes and activity timeline
- **Inline editing** + **delete** with confirmation

### ⌘K Command Palette
![Command palette with search, commands, and contact list](command_palette_1772724719406.png)

- Fuzzy search across contacts and commands
- Commands: New Contact, Show All, Contacts not talked to in 30 days
- Keyboard navigable (arrow keys + enter)

### New Contact Editor
![Clean form for creating new contacts](new_contact_editor_1772724758157.png)

- Fields: Name, Email, Phone, Company, Role, Status, LinkedIn, Tags, Notes
- Creates contact and adds to the list immediately

